HEADWORD: Dogs-tail grass
<hw>Dog's"-tail grass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A hardy species of British grass (<spn>Cynosurus
cristatus</spn>) which abounds in grass lands, and is well suited for
making straw plait; -- called also
<altname>goldseed</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dog Star</ent>⟦br⟧
